3
00:00:21,856 --> 00:00:24,316
[angin bersiul]

4
00:00:24,400 --> 00:00:27,570
[geraman parau]

5
00:00:28,696 --> 00:00:29,947
[klik]

6
00:00:33,492 --> 00:00:34,827
[angin bersiul]

7
00:00:39,290 --> 00:00:42,668
- [burung camar berteriak]
- [klakson kapal berbunyi]

8
00:00:50,634 --> 00:00:52,261
[musik mencekam]

9
00:01:06,609 --> 00:01:08,527
[musik mengancam]

10
00:01:16,368 --> 00:01:18,954
[angin menderu]

11
00:01:40,518 --> 00:01:45,356
[pintu terbuka, tertutup]

12
00:02:08,128 --> 00:02:11,632
[musik misterius]

13
00:02:21,016 --> 00:02:23,352
[geraman keras]

14
00:02:25,771 --> 00:02:26,981
[pria tertawa]

15
00:02:27,940 --> 00:02:30,901
<i>♪ Sekarang, maukah kau mendengarkan</i>
<i>Sayang ♪</i>

16
00:02:30,985 --> 00:02:33,988
<i>♪ Sementara aku berkata ♪</i>

17
00:02:34,071 --> 00:02:40,160
<i>♪ Bagaimana kau bisa bilang</i>
<i>Bahwa kau akan pergi? ♪</i>

18
00:02:40,244 --> 00:02:45,749
<i>♪ Jangan katakan kita harus berpisah ♪</i>

19
00:02:47,042 --> 00:02:48,043
Giliranmu.

20
00:02:48,127 --> 00:02:52,047
<i>♪ Jangan hancurkan</i>
<i>Hati kekasihmu ♪</i>

21
00:02:52,131 --> 00:02:57,469
<i>♪ Kau tahu aku mencintaimu</i>
<i>Selama bertahun-tahun ini ♪</i>

22
00:02:59,805 --> 00:03:00,764
Oh, begitu.

23
00:03:03,767 --> 00:03:05,686
[musik berlanjut]

24
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,985
- Mari kita lihat apa yang kau punya.
- [pria 2 tertawa kecil]

25
00:03:17,114 --> 00:03:18,866
[percakapan tidak jelas]

26
00:03:21,493 --> 00:03:22,536
[pria 1] Ayo.

27
00:03:25,205 --> 00:03:26,081
Aku?

28
00:03:26,165 --> 00:03:28,125
- [tertawa kecil]
- Sebelum aku berubah pikiran.

29
00:03:32,796 --> 00:03:35,424
Hei. Siapa yang mendapat kepingmu?

30
00:03:35,507 --> 00:03:37,134
Siapa pun yang akan
menambal lubang itu lagi.

31
00:03:37,217 --> 00:03:38,260
[para pria bergumam]

32
00:03:38,344 --> 00:03:39,345
Itu aku.

33
00:03:40,679 --> 00:03:41,847
Bagus. [mengerang]

34
00:03:42,598 --> 00:03:44,767
Wah, ini bagus.

35
00:03:44,850 --> 00:03:47,227
Mm, sebaiknya jangan
terbiasa dengan itu.

36
00:03:49,605 --> 00:03:50,648
Sebaiknya kau kecilkan itu.

37
00:03:51,190 --> 00:03:52,191
Kau akan membangunkan Sunday.

38
00:03:52,733 --> 00:03:54,818
Tidak sebelum kita menyelesaikan tarian kita.

39
00:03:54,902 --> 00:03:56,654
- Mm-hm.
- [pria 1] Kau ingat terakhir kali?

40
00:03:56,737 --> 00:03:57,947
"Pembunuhan.

41
00:03:58,989 --> 00:04:00,699
Kecilkan suara berisik itu,

42
00:04:00,783 --> 00:04:02,868
atau aku akan membeli
rumah keluargamu dan meratakannya."

43
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,411
[mengejek] "Namaku bukan..."

44
00:04:04,495 --> 00:04:05,871
[semua] "Merriell Sunday."

45
00:04:05,955 --> 00:04:07,873
[geraman keras]

46
00:04:14,964 --> 00:04:17,383
[musik rekaman berlanjut]

47
00:04:20,094 --> 00:04:22,471
[musik mengancam]

48
00:04:26,684 --> 00:04:27,726
[pria 1] Sudah memberinya makan hari ini?

49
00:04:29,561 --> 00:04:31,188
[pria 2]
Melempar makanannya ke dalam kotak.

50
00:04:31,271 --> 00:04:32,690
Kau kira aku tetap di sana
untuk memeriksa?

51
00:04:40,948 --> 00:04:42,950
[mengerang]
Cukup untukku, kawan-kawan.

52
00:04:43,993 --> 00:04:46,745
[musik berlanjut]
<i>♪ Kau akan merasa sedih... ♪</i>

53
00:04:48,998 --> 00:04:50,582
[mendengkur]

54
00:04:56,255 --> 00:04:58,257
[angin bersiul]

55
00:05:03,262 --> 00:05:04,680
[dentuman samar]

56
00:05:10,477 --> 00:05:12,604
[musik mengancam]

57
00:05:15,816 --> 00:05:17,818
[suara palu]

58
00:05:21,780 --> 00:05:22,823
Maaf.

59
00:05:22,906 --> 00:05:23,866
Ini hanya aku.

60
00:05:26,118 --> 00:05:27,119
Apa aku membangunkanmu?

61
00:05:29,830 --> 00:05:31,623
Tidak. [mengembuskan napas]

62
00:05:37,504 --> 00:05:38,380
Terima kasih.

63
00:05:42,968 --> 00:05:44,553
[palu mengetuk]

64
00:05:44,636 --> 00:05:45,929
[gemetar]

65
00:05:47,806 --> 00:05:49,433
[atap berderit]

66
00:05:49,516 --> 00:05:51,310
- [benturan keras]
- [pria 2 berteriak]

67
00:05:53,812 --> 00:05:55,481
[geraman rendah]

68
00:05:57,107 --> 00:05:59,485
[berteriak]

69
00:06:06,283 --> 00:06:08,786
[musik dramatis]

70
00:06:09,870 --> 00:06:11,914
[teriakan berlanjut]

71
00:06:13,540 --> 00:06:16,126
[reporter 1] <i>Berita terbaru:</i>
<i>Merriell Sunday Jr.,</i>

72
00:06:16,210 --> 00:06:18,879
<i>putra taipan minyak yang hilang</i>
<i>Merriell Sunday Sr.,</i>

73
00:06:18,962 --> 00:06:20,964
<i>mengadakan konferensi pers</i>
<i>darurat.</i>

74
00:06:22,382 --> 00:06:23,592
Uh...

75
00:06:23,675 --> 00:06:25,719
Halo. Uh...

76
00:06:25,803 --> 00:06:28,847
Dua minggu lalu,
Ayah dan rombongannya

77
00:06:28,931 --> 00:06:30,390
melewati batas waktu kepulangan mereka.

78
00:06:30,474 --> 00:06:34,061
Lalu, um, lewat kabel,
ada sinyal darurat.

79
00:06:34,144 --> 00:06:36,522
Kami secara resmi
menyatakan mereka hilang.

80
00:06:37,064 --> 00:06:38,649
Tapi kami tidak... kami tidak
akan membiarkan wajah

81
00:06:38,732 --> 00:06:40,692
dan pendiri Sunday Oil
menghilang begitu saja.

82
00:06:40,776 --> 00:06:41,610
Jangan khawatir.

83
00:06:41,693 --> 00:06:44,029
Aku sudah memilih sendiri
beberapa orang paling tangguh,

84
00:06:44,988 --> 00:06:47,866
para bajingan paling pintar
yang pernah Tuhan ciptakan.

85
00:06:47,950 --> 00:06:49,034
[reporter 1]
<i>Junior tidak bercanda.</i>

86
00:06:49,618 --> 00:06:52,371
<i>Leander Coates,</i>
<i>pengawas tim.</i>

87
00:06:53,038 --> 00:06:55,833
<i>Dia bertempur dalam Perang Besar</i>
<i>melawan Kaiser pada tahun '17</i>

88
00:06:55,916 --> 00:06:58,127
<i>lalu kembali lagi</i>
<i>pada tahun '44.</i>

89
00:07:00,504 --> 00:07:02,381
<i>Dr. Margaret Lamb.</i>

90
00:07:02,464 --> 00:07:04,550
<i>Dia benar-benar ahli</i>
<i>dalam urusan hewan.</i>

91
00:07:04,633 --> 00:07:06,426
<i>Dan saudari kembarnya,</i>
<i>salah satu yang hilang,</i>

92
00:07:06,510 --> 00:07:08,887
<i>pasti senang</i>
<i>dia ikut datang.</i>

93
00:07:09,847 --> 00:07:13,433
<i>Booker Marchmont,</i>
<i>ahli komunikasi radio.</i>

94
00:07:13,517 --> 00:07:15,602
<i>Dia terbang dengan Enola Gay</i>
<i>pada tahun '45,</i>

95
00:07:15,686 --> 00:07:18,105
<i>menjatuhkan bom</i>
<i>ke Jepang.</i>

96
00:07:18,188 --> 00:07:19,314
<i>Sudah terkesan?</i>

97
00:07:20,315 --> 00:07:24,570
<i>Ahli peledakan bersertifikat,</i>
<i>"Dynamite" Daniel Hewitt.</i>

98
00:07:24,653 --> 00:07:25,696
<i>Di luar sana keras,</i>

99
00:07:25,779 --> 00:07:28,073
<i>dan terkadang</i>
<i>satu-satunya jalan menembusnya</i>

100
00:07:28,157 --> 00:07:29,950
<i>adalah dengan segenggam bubuk peledak.</i>

101
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,785
[bel berbunyi]

102
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,672
Orang-orang yang membuat peta pertama.

103
00:07:45,132 --> 00:07:47,968
Mereka adalah para raksasa
yang mengarungi tujuh lautan

104
00:07:48,051 --> 00:07:49,720
dan menjelajahi dunia,

105
00:07:50,429 --> 00:07:53,182
membelah jalan
menembus hutan dengan parang,

106
00:07:53,265 --> 00:07:55,976
membakar jalan melalui gua
penuh sarang laba-laba dengan obor

107
00:07:56,727 --> 00:08:00,898
dengan ego yang hampir pasti
tak tertahankan.

108
00:08:03,358 --> 00:08:06,945
Kartografi dan penjelajahan
bukanlah hal yang sama.

109
00:08:08,739 --> 00:08:10,741
Kalian belum pernah mendengar
kebanyakan pembuat peta.

110
00:08:12,451 --> 00:08:16,788
Mereka melakukan penjelajahan
pada malam hari, dalam gelap

111
00:08:17,789 --> 00:08:18,665
dengan lilin.

112
00:08:20,083 --> 00:08:21,793
Obor mereka, pena.

113
00:08:22,711 --> 00:08:24,713
Kapal mereka, buku.

114
00:08:26,340 --> 00:08:27,633
Florence Kelley

115
00:08:27,716 --> 00:08:30,761
menciptakan metode baru
untuk memvisualisasikan data

116
00:08:30,844 --> 00:08:33,388
ketika... ketika dia memetakan
daerah kumuh Chicago, dan...

117
00:08:34,139 --> 00:08:37,142
dia melakukannya tanpa mendaki
ke negeri jauh.

118
00:08:38,560 --> 00:08:39,811
Maksudku begini...

119
00:08:40,646 --> 00:08:43,440
Kau tidak perlu meninggalkan rumah
untuk menjadi pelopor.

120
00:08:44,942 --> 00:08:46,610
- [student batuk]
- [chair rattles]

121
00:08:46,693 --> 00:08:47,444
Ya?

122
00:08:48,320 --> 00:08:51,114
Benarkah ayahmu
terjebak di piramida?

123
00:08:53,700 --> 00:08:55,452
[bel berbunyi]

124
00:08:58,205 --> 00:08:59,206
[murid] Bu.

125
00:09:00,874 --> 00:09:01,959
Maukah Ibu menandatangani ini?

126
00:09:04,795 --> 00:09:05,671
[menghela napas]

127
00:09:08,423 --> 00:09:09,967
[murid]
Ayahmu adalah pahlawanku.

128
00:09:10,050 --> 00:09:11,718
[wanita] Miss Bannister
ada rapat sekarang.

129
00:09:15,055 --> 00:09:16,014
Terima kasih.

130
00:09:16,098 --> 00:09:18,100
Terima kasih. Aku, uh...

131
00:09:18,183 --> 00:09:19,393
Akulah rapatmu berikutnya.

132
00:09:20,644 --> 00:09:22,688
Maaf menyergap begini.
Namaku Belle Parker.

133
00:09:22,771 --> 00:09:24,731
Aku mewakili
Tuan Merriell Sunday Jr.

134
00:09:28,318 --> 00:09:29,486
[Parker]
Kau tahu kenapa aku kemari?

135
00:09:30,862 --> 00:09:32,030
Aku bisa menebak.

136
00:09:32,114 --> 00:09:33,448
Ini tentang ayahmu.

137
00:09:33,532 --> 00:09:34,533
[Ellie tertawa] Tema hari ini.

138
00:09:35,492 --> 00:09:37,452
Kurasa ini serius,
Miss Bannister.

139
00:09:37,536 --> 00:09:39,830
Aku yakin begitu. [menghela napas]

140
00:09:39,913 --> 00:09:42,749
Apakah dia menginjak pintu jebakan
dan jatuh ke lubang ular?

141
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,960
Kau tahu tentang ekspedisinya
ke wilayah Alaska?

142
00:09:45,043 --> 00:09:47,337
Dipanggang di tusukan
oleh sekelompok penduduk lokal?

143
00:09:47,421 --> 00:09:49,131
Dia dan tim Sunday
hilang.

144
00:09:49,798 --> 00:09:51,800
Hollis sudah hilang
sejak aku berusia 15 tahun.

145
00:09:52,843 --> 00:09:53,677
Dia tidak hilang.

146
00:09:53,760 --> 00:09:55,721
Dia... tepat
di tempat yang dia inginkan.

147
00:09:56,388 --> 00:09:59,182
Kapalnya pergi,
dan mereka tertinggal.

148
00:10:00,183 --> 00:10:02,477
Dan kabar terakhir yang diterima kapal
adalah SOS.

149
00:10:07,316 --> 00:10:08,525
Apa yang harus
kulakukan tentang itu?

150
00:10:09,609 --> 00:10:12,821
Tuan Merriell Sunday Jr. sedang
membentuk tim penyelamat.

151
00:10:14,323 --> 00:10:15,866
Menyelamatkan ayahnya dan ayahmu juga.

152
00:10:17,117 --> 00:10:18,827
Dan dia ingin kau
memimpin pencariannya.

153
00:10:21,121 --> 00:10:22,581
Kau berbakat dalam sesuatu,

154
00:10:22,664 --> 00:10:24,458
tapi kau tak pernah
sempat menggunakannya.

155
00:10:27,711 --> 00:10:29,171
Tidakkah menurutmu ini saatnya?

156
00:10:29,254 --> 00:10:31,089
[musik termenung]

157
00:10:34,301 --> 00:10:36,094
Jika sesuatu terjadi di sana,

158
00:10:37,971 --> 00:10:39,348
dan Hollis benar-benar dalam masalah,

159
00:10:39,431 --> 00:10:41,391
bagaimana menurutmu
kalian semua akan bertahan?

160
00:10:42,142 --> 00:10:43,852
Lebih baik bersamamu.

161
00:10:49,858 --> 00:10:51,068
Hei, tunggu.

162
00:10:55,906 --> 00:10:57,282
Itu benda terakhir
yang Hollis berikan kepadaku.

163
00:11:01,828 --> 00:11:02,954
Kau akan membutuhkannya.

164
00:11:07,084 --> 00:11:09,461
[musik sendu]

165
00:11:13,965 --> 00:11:16,385
- [pintu tertutup]
- [langkah kaki menjauh]

166
00:11:19,429 --> 00:11:21,515
[musik sendu berlanjut]

167
00:11:38,990 --> 00:11:40,992
[musik piano lembut]

168
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:49,626
[laci dibanting]

169
00:11:51,586 --> 00:11:53,880
[musik penuh tekad]

170
00:11:55,298 --> 00:11:56,216
[Sunday Jr.]
<i>Aku sudah menyewa</i>

171
00:11:56,299 --> 00:11:58,051
<i>navigator terbaik</i>
<i>yang tersisa di Selatan.</i>

172
00:11:59,219 --> 00:12:01,096
<i>Dia akan membuat semuanya</i>
<i>lebih mudah bagi kita.</i>

173
00:12:01,179 --> 00:12:02,931
[reporter 2] <i>Tunggu, "dia" perempuan?</i>
<i>Kau baru saja bilang "dia"?</i>

174
00:12:03,014 --> 00:12:03,890
[reporter 3] <i>Siapa dia?</i>

175
00:12:06,143 --> 00:12:09,187
[musik dramatis]

176
00:12:10,021 --> 00:12:11,565
[Sunday Jr.]
Izinkan aku mempersembahkan navigator kita,

177
00:12:12,232 --> 00:12:14,484
- Miss Ellie Bannister.
- [keributan]

178
00:12:14,568 --> 00:12:15,902
[Sunday Jr.] Tidak ada pertanyaan lagi,

179
00:12:15,986 --> 00:12:17,654
atau Coates akan mengeluarkan kalian
lewat pintu dengan kepala kalian dulu.

180
00:12:17,737 --> 00:12:18,738
Kita selesai di sini.

181
00:12:30,709 --> 00:12:31,751
Tapi kita ambil senter.

182
00:12:38,008 --> 00:12:39,468
[bunyi rana kamera]

183
00:12:39,551 --> 00:12:41,636
[angin bersiul]

184
00:12:42,429 --> 00:12:44,764
[pepohonan berderit]

185
00:12:51,563 --> 00:12:54,691
Erebus. Ini Ellie.
Aku perlu ping lokasi kami.

186
00:12:55,233 --> 00:12:56,151
Kau dengar?

187
00:12:56,234 --> 00:12:58,737
[statis radio terputus-putus]

188
00:12:58,820 --> 00:13:01,323
[Erebus] <i>...sebuah jangkar...</i>
<i>Kau bisa mendengarku? Ganti.</i>

189
00:13:01,406 --> 00:13:03,450
Erebus. Masuk.

190
00:13:03,533 --> 00:13:04,784
Badai sedang melewati kapal.

191
00:13:05,494 --> 00:13:07,746
Ulangi... ulangi.
Kapan kalian akan kembali?

192
00:13:09,456 --> 00:13:10,540
Maaf, Miss Bannister.

193
00:13:10,624 --> 00:13:12,125
Hujan deras ini
membuat kami terjebak

194
00:13:12,209 --> 00:13:13,168
beberapa hari terakhir.

195
00:13:18,507 --> 00:13:20,800
[Dan] Tanah sialan ini lebih keras
daripada Paman Tommy.

196
00:13:20,884 --> 00:13:22,469
[ketukan]

197
00:13:24,513 --> 00:13:25,722
[mengembuskan napas]

198
00:13:29,559 --> 00:13:30,727
Sialan.

199
00:13:35,690 --> 00:13:37,025
[Lamb] Kau akan membutuhkan
lebih dari sekadar sekop.

200
00:13:37,901 --> 00:13:42,447
Lapisan atas itu permafrost.
Padat seperti batu sampai pertengahan musim panas.

201
00:13:42,531 --> 00:13:45,408
Rasanya seperti mencoba meninju
landasan besi.

202
00:13:47,577 --> 00:13:49,120
- [Sunday Jr.] Hei. Hei.
- Coba untuk--

203
00:13:49,204 --> 00:13:50,497
[Sunday Jr.] Kau sudah tahu
kita menuju ke mana?

204
00:13:50,580 --> 00:13:51,581
Tunggu, tunggu, tunggu. Berdiri.

205
00:13:51,665 --> 00:13:53,416
Bangun, bangun, kalian.
Berkumpul. Ayo.

206
00:13:55,669 --> 00:13:57,003
Ayo. Beri tahu kami.

207
00:13:58,129 --> 00:14:00,257
Kami berhasil menghubungi Erebus.

208
00:14:00,340 --> 00:14:02,133
Tapi badai...
Sinyalnya tidak--

209
00:14:02,217 --> 00:14:04,052
- Aku tidak mendengar solusi.
- Aku tidak tahu.

210
00:14:05,845 --> 00:14:07,472
Dengan badai ini, aku tidak bisa...

211
00:14:07,556 --> 00:14:09,516
[Ellie menghela napas]
Kita harus tetap di tempat

212
00:14:09,599 --> 00:14:11,560
sampai badai berlalu.

213
00:14:11,643 --> 00:14:13,520
Lalu kita bisa terus bergerak.

214
00:14:13,603 --> 00:14:14,646
[Dan] Oh, astaga.

215
00:14:15,730 --> 00:14:17,440
Tetap di tempat? Di... di apa?

216
00:14:18,108 --> 00:14:19,734
Kaleng sup?

217
00:14:19,818 --> 00:14:21,069
Kita sudah berputar-putar

218
00:14:21,152 --> 00:14:22,988
mengikuti si gadis ini
selama tiga hari!

219
00:14:23,071 --> 00:14:24,281
[Parker] Ini karena badai.

220
00:14:24,364 --> 00:14:26,408
- Tak ada yang tahu kita di mana.
- Kita akan mati di sini

221
00:14:26,491 --> 00:14:28,577
- jika kita tinggal lebih lama.
- Cukup.

